                    <b>OK, what does a credit get me?</b><br>
                    A bank rule reconciliation costs one credit and a SmartMatch reconciliation costs four. A
                    GuidedMatch reconciliation is absolutely free.
                </p>
                <p class="leading-[1.75em] mt-3">
                    You can decide to enable or disable bank rule reconciliations, and SmartMatch reconciliations, for
                    any client; you're in complete control.
                </p>
                <p class="leading-[1.75em] mt-3">
                    Not only that, you can choose between fixed or overage pricing. With fixed, you pay the amount of
                    your plan at the beginning of the month and Otto will stop reconciling if you run out of credits.
                    He'll start again when the next monthly payment is taken. With overage you'll just pay for any
                    credits outside of your allowance at the end of the month. For example, if you're on plan C and use
                    a total of 550 credits, you'd pay £10 for the extra 50 credits.
                </p>
